90, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Thomas de Fixby was born about 1217, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 daughters with Thomas de Fixby."},"et":{"about 1217–":"umbes 1217–Surnud","1217–Male":"1217–Surnud","1238–1263":"1238–1263","1262–Female":"1262–Surnud","1217–Female":"1217–Surnud","1217":"1217","1238":"1238","about 1217":"umbes 1217","Abt 1238":"umbes 1238","1263":"1263","1262":"1262","Huddersfield, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Huddersfield, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Fixby, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Fixby, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1217–":"noin 1217–Kuollut","1217–Male":"1217–Kuollut","1238–1263":"1238–1263","1262–Female":"1262–Kuollut","1217–Female":"1217–Kuollut","1217":"1217","1238":"1238","about 1217":"noin 1217","Abt 1238":"noin 1238","1263":"1263","1262":"1262","Huddersfield, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Huddersfield, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Fixby, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Fixby, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1217–":"environ 1217–Décédée","1217–Male":"1217–Décédé","1238–1263":"1238–1263","1262–Female":"1262–Décédée","1217–Female":"1217–Décédée","1217":"1217","1238":"1238","about 1217":"environ 1217","Abt 1238":"environ 1238","1263":"1263","1262":"1262","Huddersfield, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Huddersfield, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","of Yorkshire, E